## ty — Type Checker

[ty](https://docs.astral.sh/ty/) is Astral's new type checker (10-100x faster than mypy). It is in active development (alpha as of March 2026) but already valuable for `exodus-core` and `ironlayer_oss`.

### Usage

```bash
uv run ty check                 # Check current project
uvx ty check src/               # Run ephemerally
```

### Config

```toml
# pyproject.toml
[tool.ty]
# Enable strict mode for new code
strict = false           # Start permissive, tighten per-module

# Environment discovery
python-version = "3.11"

[[tool.ty.overrides]]
module = "databricks.*"
ignore-missing-imports = true
```

### Migration Path from mypy

1. `exodus-core` and `ironlayer_oss` — add `ty check` to CI now (alongside mypy during transition)
2. Other repos — add when mypy coverage is >60%
3. Once ty is stable, remove mypy; ty becomes the sole type checker

### VS Code / Cursor Integration

Add to workspace settings to enable ty language server:

```json
"python.analysis.typeCheckingMode": "off",  // disable Pylance type checking
"[python]": {
    "editor.defaultFormatter": "charliermarsh.ruff"  // Ruff handles formatting
}
```

ty installs its own language server automatically when installed via `uv tool install ty`.

